The paper discusses the analysis of literature in the domain of Clinical Decision Support Systems (CDSS) using complex network-based analytical models. This involves the use of data mining, machine learning, and information retrieval techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.DL (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also focuses on the application of CDSS in healthcare, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction in Healthcare). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of CDSS research in different countries and universities, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computational Social Science).
